<paragraph id="553F36FEFF87F93CEDD248E8FA09F8A1" blockId="4.[136,1452,1708,1987]" pageId="4" pageNumber="71">
Description:— 
<taxonomicName id="92804D7DFF87F93CEC7448E8FE19F91D" authorityName="Corda" authorityYear="1842" box="[302,412,1708,1734]" class="Incertae sedis" family="Incertae sedis" genus="Mycelium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" order="Incertae sedis" pageId="4" pageNumber="71" phylum="Incertae sedis" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="67F4EAECFF87F93CEC7448E8FE19F91D" box="[302,412,1708,1734]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="71">Mycelium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
consisting of smooth, subhyaline to brown, branched, thin-walled, septate, 2–4 µm diam hyphae. 
<emphasis id="67F4EAECFF87F93CEDB34894FE0BF931" box="[233,398,1744,1770]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="71">Conidiophores</emphasis>
macronematous, mononematous, solitary, branched at the apex, scattered, wider at the base, erect, brown, paler and slightly tapering upward, straight or slightly flexuous, smooth, septate, cylindrical, 50–372 × 4.5–9.5 μm. 
<emphasis id="67F4EAECFF87F93CEC43495CFE7BF8E9" box="[281,510,1816,1842]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="71">Conidiogenous cells</emphasis>
integrated, terminal, cylindrical or lageniform to ampulliform, with a conspicuous outer collarette, subhyaline to pale brown, smooth, 5.0–10 × 2.0–3.5 µm. 
<emphasis id="67F4EAECFF87F93CEE9A4978FB9FF88D" box="[960,1050,1852,1878]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="71">Conidia</emphasis>
obovoid or ellipsoidal, acrogenous, subhyaline to pale brown, solitary, aseptate, guttulate, thin-walled, 2.5–5.0 × 2–2.5 μm. Sexual stage not observed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="553F36FEFF87F93CEDE749C0FCD0F819" blockId="4.[136,1452,1708,1987]" pageId="4" pageNumber="71">
Culture characteristics:—Colonies on PDA effuse, thinly hairy, with sparse to moderate aerial hypha, pale to medium brown, reaching 
<quantity id="92789B1BFF87F93CECF249ECFE72F818" box="[424,503,1960,1987]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="71" unit="mm" value="20.0">20 mm</quantity>
diam at 25 ± 1 °C after 7 days.
</paragraph>
<caption id="01FF6676FF86F93DEDD24A9AFB77FAC3" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6605367" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6605367" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6605367/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="72" startId="5.[136,229,1246,1268]" targetBox="[178,1416,200,1219]" targetPageId="5">
<paragraph id="553F36FEFF86F93DEDD24A9AFB77FAC3" blockId="5.[136,1451,1246,1304]" pageId="5" pageNumber="72">
<emphasis id="67F4EAECFF86F93DEDD24A9AFF7BFB28" bold="true" box="[136,254,1246,1268]" pageId="5" pageNumber="72">FIGURE 3.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="92804D7DFF86F93DEC5E4A9AFE79FB2F" authorityName="K. Y. Wang, T. P. Wei &amp; Y. L. Jiang" authorityYear="2022" box="[260,508,1246,1268]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Chaetosphaeriaceae" genus="Chloridium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Chaetosphaeriales" pageId="5" pageNumber="72" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="paucisetosum">
<emphasis id="67F4EAECFF86F93DEC5E4A9AFE79FB2F" box="[260,508,1246,1268]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="72">Chloridium paucisetosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(CGMCC3.19620). A–B: Colony on PDA for 2 weeks. C–D: Conidiophores, conidiogenous cells and conidia. E: Conidiogenous cells producing conidia. F: Conidia. Scale bars: C = 100 μm; D–E = 10 μm; F = 5 μm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="553F36FEFF86F93DEDE74B03FD37F95A" blockId="5.[136,1452,1351,1665]" pageId="5" pageNumber="72">
Notes:— 
<taxonomicName id="92804D7DFF86F93DEC784B03FDC1FABA" authorityName="K. Y. Wang, T. P. Wei &amp; Y. L. Jiang" authorityYear="2022" box="[290,580,1351,1377]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Chaetosphaeriaceae" genus="Chloridium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Chaetosphaeriales" pageId="5" pageNumber="72" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="paucisetosum">
<emphasis id="67F4EAECFF86F93DEC784B03FDC1FABA" box="[290,580,1351,1377]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="72">Chloridium paucisetosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
shares a few morphological similarities with 
<taxonomicName id="92804D7DFF86F93DE9104B03FB67FABA" box="[1098,1250,1351,1377]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Chaetosphaeriaceae" genus="Sporoschisma" kingdom="Fungi" order="Chaetosphaeriales" pageId="5" pageNumber="72" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="aquaticum">
<emphasis id="67F4EAECFF86F93DE9104B03FB67FABA" box="[1098,1250,1351,1377]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="72">C. aquaticum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="92804D7DFF86F93DE9AB4B03FAFEFABA" box="[1265,1403,1351,1377]" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Mollisiaceae" genus="Phialocephala" kingdom="Fungi" order="Helotiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="72" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="humicola">
<emphasis id="67F4EAECFF86F93DE9AB4B03FAFEFABA" box="[1265,1403,1351,1377]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="72">C. humicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="92804D7DFF86F93DEDD24B2FFE95FA5E" box="[136,272,1387,1413]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" genus="Carpinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="5" pageNumber="72" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="terricola">
<emphasis id="67F4EAECFF86F93DEDD24B2FFE95FA5E" box="[136,272,1387,1413]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="72">C. terricola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having branched conidiophores and phialidic conidiogenous cells. Nevertheless, 
<taxonomicName id="92804D7DFF86F93DE9B74B2FFA2EFA5E" authorityName="K. Y. Wang, T. P. Wei &amp; Y. L. Jiang" authorityYear="2022" box="[1261,1451,1387,1413]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Chaetosphaeriaceae" genus="Chloridium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Chaetosphaeriales" pageId="5" pageNumber="72" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="paucisetosum">
<emphasis id="67F4EAECFF86F93DE9B74B2FFA2EFA5E" box="[1261,1451,1387,1413]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="72">C. paucisetosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
showed high heterogeneity, forming a monophyletic clade, which was genetically distant from all species (
<figureCitation id="CDBB2A7BFF86F93DE80C4BCBFA1FFA72" box="[1366,1434,1423,1449]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[136,229,1824,1846]" captionTargetBox="[199,1408,886,1786]" captionTargetId="figure-270@3.[151,1436,868,1796]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Phylogram of RAxML analysis based on a combined ITS and LSU sequence dataset within Chloridium. Adautomilanezia caesalpiniae was used as outgroup. Bootstrap support values for Maximum likelihood and Maximum parsimony greater than 50%, and Bayesian posterior probabilities equal to or greater than 0.8 are indicated at the nodes (ML/BI/MP). Type strains are highlighted by a “*”, and our strain is in bold." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6605363" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6605363/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="72">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Morphologically, 
<taxonomicName id="92804D7DFF86F93DEC0F4BF7FD97FA16" authorityName="K. Y. Wang, T. P. Wei &amp; Y. L. Jiang" authorityYear="2022" box="[341,530,1459,1485]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Chaetosphaeriaceae" genus="Chloridium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Chaetosphaeriales" pageId="5" pageNumber="72" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="paucisetosum">
<emphasis id="67F4EAECFF86F93DEC0F4BF7FD97FA16" box="[341,530,1459,1485]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="72">C. paucisetosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can also be distinguished from these species. 
<taxonomicName id="92804D7DFF86F93DE9624BF7FABEFA16" box="[1080,1339,1459,1485]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Chaetosphaeriaceae" genus="Chloridium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Chaetosphaeriales" pageId="5" pageNumber="72" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="aquaticum">
<emphasis id="67F4EAECFF86F93DE9624BF7FABEFA16" box="[1080,1339,1459,1485]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="72">Chloridium aquaticum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
produces ellipsoidal to cylindrical conidia in slimy masses (
<bibRefCitation id="31114B0FFF86F93DEF9E4B93FCFEFA2A" author="Wei, M. J. &amp; Zhang, H. &amp; Dong, W. E. I. &amp; Boonmee, S. &amp; Zhang, D. I." box="[708,891,1495,1521]" pageId="5" pageNumber="72" pagination="187 - 199" refId="ref7162" refString="Wei, M. J., Zhang, H., Dong, W. E. I., Boonmee, S. &amp; Zhang, D. I. (2018) Introducing Dictyochaeta aquatica sp. nov. and two new species of Chloridium (Chaetosphaeriaceae, Sordariomycetes) from aquatic habitats. Phytotaxa 362 (2): 187 - 199. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 362.2.5" type="journal article" year="2018">
Wei 
<emphasis id="67F4EAECFF86F93DEFA14B9CFCABFA2A" box="[763,814,1495,1521]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="72">et al</emphasis>
. 2018
</bibRefCitation>
); The conidia of the 
<taxonomicName id="92804D7DFF86F93DE9334B93FB76FA2A" box="[1129,1267,1495,1521]" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Mollisiaceae" genus="Phialocephala" kingdom="Fungi" order="Helotiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="72" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="humicola">
<emphasis id="67F4EAECFF86F93DE9334B93FB76FA2A" box="[1129,1267,1495,1521]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="72">C. humicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are aggregating in hyaline slimy masses and smaller (2.7–3.6 × 1.5–2.0 µm), as well as longer conidiophores (700 × 8.0 µm; 
<bibRefCitation id="31114B0FFF86F93DE8034BBFFE88F9E2" author="Jong, S. C. &amp; Davis, E. E." pageId="5" pageNumber="72" pagination="1351 - 1356" refId="ref5627" refString="Jong, S. C. &amp; Davis, E. E. (1972) Phialocephala humicola, a new hyphomycete. Mycologia 64 (6): 1351 - 1356. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00275514.1972.12019390" type="journal article" year="1972">Jong &amp; Davis 1972</bibRefCitation>
); 
<taxonomicName id="92804D7DFF86F93DEC78485BFE23F9E2" box="[290,422,1567,1593]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" genus="Carpinus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="5" pageNumber="72" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="terricola">
<emphasis id="67F4EAECFF86F93DEC78485BFE23F9E2" box="[290,422,1567,1593]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="72">C. terricola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs by its truncate at the base and smaller conidia (2–3 × 2–2.5 µm; 
<bibRefCitation id="31114B0FFF86F93DE980485BFA25F9E2" author="Wang, Y. &amp; Jie, C. Y. &amp; Hyde, K. D. &amp; Jiang, Y. L. &amp; Zhang, T. Y. &amp; Zhao, D. G." box="[1242,1440,1567,1593]" pageId="5" pageNumber="72" pagination="79 - 86" refId="ref7091" refString="Wang, Y., Jie, C. Y., Hyde, K. D., Jiang, Y. L., Zhang, T. Y. &amp; Zhao, D. G. (2017) Chloridium terricola sp. nov. from China. Mycotaxon 132 (1): 79 - 86. https: // doi. org / 10.5248 / 132.79" type="journal article" year="2017">
Wang 
<emphasis id="67F4EAECFF86F93DE8784864FAD1F9E2" box="[1314,1364,1567,1593]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="72">et al</emphasis>
. 2017
</bibRefCitation>
). Furthermore, The PHI tests revealed that no evidence of recombination (Фw = 0.2545) was detected between 
<taxonomicName id="92804D7DFF86F93DE8C84807FEA5F95A" authorityName="K. Y. Wang, T. P. Wei &amp; Y. L. Jiang" authorityYear="2022" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Chaetosphaeriaceae" genus="Chloridium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Chaetosphaeriales" pageId="5" pageNumber="72" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="paucisetosum">
<emphasis id="67F4EAECFF86F93DE8C84807FEA5F95A" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="72">C. paucisetosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and its closely related taxa (
<figureCitation id="CDBB2A7BFF86F93DEF3A4823FD20F95A" box="[608,677,1639,1665]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[136,229,1227,1249]" captionTargetBox="[183,1395,224,1184]" captionTargetId="figure-24@4.[151,1436,190,1203]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Splitgraphs showing the results of the pairwise homoplasy index (PHI) test of newly described taxa and closely related species using both LogDet transformation and splits decomposition. PHI test results (Φw) &lt;0.05 indicate significant recombination within the dataset. Type strains and new taxa are indicated with “*” and bold, respectively." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6605365" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6605365/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="72">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
